race.comment: TRANSATLANTIC (1) Tony Gollan-trained gelding who was rewarded for his consistency when a game on pace winner of the G1 Toorak Handicap at Caulfield over the 1600m. Huge drop in grade and is going much better than the bulk of these. SALTCOATS (10) sharp drop in trip and kept fresh after taking out the LR Wyong Gold Cup over 2100m on September 8. Since given a 1050m trial at Randwick. Watch for him late if they overdo it up front. CAFE MILLENIUM (9) the Hayes' team have found the key to this hulking gelding with the three wins and a minor placing since taking the reins. Will go back from the gate and Gaudray is building a good association with him. LES VAMPIRES (11) disappointed first-up but this suits much better. He's got a great second-up record and sharp improvement wouldn't surprise.
